On Wednesday Trade, Industry and Competition Minister Ebrahim Patel gazetted directions on the sale of winter clothing, footwear and bedding during Level 4 lockdown. The publication of these directions results from Patel’s consultative meeting with industry leaders in the Clothing, Textile, Footwear and Leather sector, held last week. INFOGRAPHIC: Winter clothing permitted to be bought at retail stores. sabcnews.com | SABC News channel | SABC Radio news SA COVID-19 LOCKDOWN WINTER CLOTHING All baby and toddler clothing and footwear PERMITTED Trade, Industry and Competition Minister Ebrahim Patel has gazetted directions on the sale of winter clothing LEVEL 4 Source: South African government LEVEL 4 Dresses  Skirts Active wear, including gym, running and other exercise apparel All maternity wear All adult sleepwear and gowns  All adult underwear Footwear Boots Slippers Closed-toe shoes Sneakers & trainers Knitwear Jackets and coats  Denim jackets Outerwear  Footwear  Socks  Related accessories Underwear  Sleepwear School wear  School shoes  All children’s clothing LEVEL 4 Adults Clothing Long-sleeved tops  Long-sleeved t-shirts Pants Leggings  Crop bottoms   Leggings Short-sleeved knit tops   Short-sleeved t-shirts One pieces such as bodysuits Adult accessories: Shawls and scarves, beanies, gloves, socks, belts, headwear, accessories, hair accessories Short or long-sleeved shirts & golf shirts Baby bedding and blankets Duvets, Duvet inners  Comforters  Quilts  Blankets  Electric blankets Mattress protectors  Pillows & pillow cases  Throws  Sheets    Bedding Categories (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document));